Reverse engineer form submission and fetch export data from Nigerian Bureau of Statistics (https://nigerianstat.gov.ng)¶

In [104]:
def fetch_export_data(year):
    url = "https://nigerianstat.gov.ng/tradestat/queryDb"
    payload = f"tradeflow=export&option=items&year={year}&hs_item_code=&country_code="
    headers = {
        'content-type': "application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
        'cache-control': "no-cache"
        }
    response = requests.request("POST", url, data=payload, headers=headers)
    return response.text
In [ ]:
def process_export_html(export_html):
    soup_table = BeautifulSoup(export_html,'lxml')
    row_list = [t_row.find_all('td') for t_row in soup_table.find_all('tr')]
    return [[year,column[1].contents[0],column[2].contents[0],column[3].contents[0]] for column in row_list if len(column)==4]

export_data = []
for year in years:
    print(f'Processing {year}')
    year_data = fetch_export_data(year)
    export_data.extend(process_export_html(year_data))
export_df = pd.DataFrame(export_data,columns=['year','code','description','value'])
export_df.to_csv('export_data.csv',index=False)

A grim tale of oil addiction and a struggling agricultural sector¶

  • The top 10 exports of the last 20 years has been dominated by raw crude oil/gas products taken straight from the ground loaded into ships and exported.
  • This highlights the story of the Nigerian government doing the barest minimum to generate revenue.
  • 7 of the top 10 exports in 2014 were crude oil/gas related products.
  • Sesamum seeds and Cocoa beans are the only agricultural products that appear consistently in the top 10 exports.
  • 2011 - 2012 saw a rise in rubber exports, the export value of rubber dropped significantly in 2013 and disappeared from the top 10 by 2014.
